Frosin Loneshadow<br>
Assassin on Lanys <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utzutentsunami.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzuten Tsunami</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 9:56:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quick Tormax Faction.</span><hr size=1> To answer a few question.<br>
<br>
Hunting Royals - Tried that one night killed about 8. Bad side, you need a good group there to do it. Most are not really keen on the idea of spending days on end, when they can be raiding.<br>
<br>
Dorf Heads - This is something I can do solo, while letting the rest of my guild continue their raiding.<br>
<br>
From max KOS: Dain + yel + 8 royals +1 Chamberlin + 210 Dorf Heads = Ally to Tormax. (woot..took 4 days)<br>
<br>
The main reason I am getting ally to Tormax is that I have a Dain head in my bag, and need to turn in to Tormax himself for my new belt.<br>
<br>
I know, people say &quot;you only need amiable/kindly/warmly for the quest..&quot; But I would hate to see this happen....when I turn in my Dain Head..<br>
<br>
 . . .<br>
<br>
<br>
Yup that is the sound of nada... zip...nothing. *Grins*<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utzutentsunami.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzuten Tsunami</A> at: 11/27/01 9:57:58 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubigmeeno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bigmeeno</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 12:03:37 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quick Tormax Faction.</span><hr size=1> Getting faction from the Royal Guards in Icewell Keep is by far the fastest way to get Tormax faction, aside from killing Dain and Yelinek.<br>
<br>
What I did was to attend several raids where the guilds were trying Dain, and cast a low level spell on each and every Royal Guard that was pulled in order to get on their hate lists, which results in getting faction from each one.<br>
<br>
Multiple groups (55+ recommended) can also go up on the second floor in Icewell Keep and farm the Royals for faction, especially when the Dain isnt up. The Royal Guards respawn fairly quickly giving tons of faction for a few hours of farming.<br>
<br>
Even with having attended a few failed Dain raids to kill Royal Guards, I ended up needing to turn in roughly 100 coldain heads (farmed in the Coldain mines in GD) as well before I finally maxed out my ally faction with Tormax. This was with never having killed Giants. So if you killed Giants, expect to have to do more.<br>
<br>
How much faction you need with Tormax depends on what you want to do with him. To get ToV armor, unless you are a shaman, you can get past the Tormax mobs in his room even when KoS. Unfortunately, the Shaman quest giver has a Tormax faction mob standing right next to it, so shaman must get to at least dubious.<br>
<br>
To get the Frostbringer or Cloak, you will need at least High amiable, and since you cant really tell where you are, I suggest Kindly, Warmly or Ally to be safe.<br>
<br>
And you need to be ally with Tormax to turn in Dains head from what I hear.. Still waiting to actually be able to get the head myself. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utzutentsunami.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzuten Tsunami</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 4:15:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quick Tormax Faction.</span><hr size=1> well.. I was on a time constraint... there are 3 guilds that do Tormax.. if I did not turn in the item today... would be a few weeks before I would see him....<br>
